Patrick Anderson >>>My short answer is that the GPL is enforced between instance owners (who are initially also the workers) for the purpose of insuring Freedom for every User.  RMS and Moglen speak of "User Freedom", never of "Worker Freedom" or "Owner Freedom".  The GNU General Public License is not an EULA.  GPLv2 says "Activities other than copying, distribution and modification are not covered by this License; they are outside its scope."

